ut into pieces (3 cm)","900 g water","2 tsp Chicken stock paste (refer to The Basic Cookbook)","1 fresh green chilli (e.g. jalapeño), deseeded if preferred and cut into pieces (optional)","200 - 300 g thickened cream","½ tsp salt","½ tsp ground cumin","½ tsp ground sweet paprika","2 tbsp fresh coriander, leaves only, cut into pieces"]}],"id":"r156151","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-5nPmR2GjbTw\/XZMz277pLnI\/AAAAAAAAa2M\/loIRhP_B6ssiWp-_iuAsmgcegW_cbhLHwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lep3mBbP7kMUGns1.png","title":"Chicken corn chowder with broccoli terrines","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"19 g","fat":"27 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"10 g","calories":"1537 kJ \/ 367 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ramekins (7 cm)","hintsAndTricks":["To keep the broccoli terrines warm while you enjoy the chowder, set the covered Varoma with the broccoli terrines on the empty but still warm mixing bowl.<br>- Turn out terrines onto a plate for an attractive presentation.<br>- Broccoli terrines can also be served as a starter or as a side dish with smoked salmon or roasted meat.<br>- Instead of ceramic ramekins, use glass jars or metal moulds. If using metal moulds, reduce cooking time by <nobr>2 minutes<\/nobr> in <nobr>step 7.<\/nobr>"],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","1h 25m","8 portions"]}